  - export function fizzBuzzRange(start: number, end: number, options?: { variant?: 'standard'|'digit'|'custom', customDivisors?: Array<{divisor:number,label:string}>, output?: 'array'|'generator'|'stream' }) : (Array<number|string>|Iterable<number|string>)
  - export function fizzBuzzSingle(n: number): number|string
- Validation rules:
  - Throw TypeError when input is NaN, not typeof 'number', or not finite.
  - Throw RangeError if start > end or if range length exceeds a configurable maxRange option to avoid DoS (e.g., maxRange default 1e7).
- Implementation pattern:
  - Prefer r3 and r5 boolean checks computed via (n % 3 === 0) and (n % 5 === 0) to minimize modulus operations (or compute r15 = n % 15 === 0 for single check).
  - For custom divisors, compute labels by iterating divisor array and concatenating when n % divisor === 0.

